I do wanna add to my last post that the psychiatrist that work in this country always have to balance a limbo for their patients, which I am grateful for. I have had stories in many court cases just for people coming back from western countries and put in jail
Living in a communism torn country, poor economy and heavy ableism and racism really changes your view on western countries.

To have papers means to be treated like an unequal adult among society and no free choices in work spaces nor health care or transport. Without offical paperwork i am unable to finish work, education or go through daily life without facing a struggle.

To have official disability paperwork means I am removed from driving a car and many other daily activities others can enjoy due to this countries legal system... Without legal paperwork I cannot work or finish education... I hope things change in this country soon.

Sorry for long inactivity. I got in contact with my psychiatrist after months. There was alot tears over disability again. I need to sort it out with him. Its been really long time until I could speak to family and bring out these issues again into the air.

What i'm saying is, If you had death in your childhood and you didn't process it, and you only understood the way a child would aka that person left and wont come back anymore. You will have issues with people leaving because you will respond to the trigger in childhood way.
It's not nessecarily toxic in itself, but avoidance, defensiveness, shutting down when another person who is not toxic triggers this can appear toxic.

AND DON'T use self diagnosis for purposeful intended harm on another person, or excuse for action which you choose to do/not to. A choice to do something is conscious, but unintended harm and unawareness of it could be a sign of something more.

All in all in summary, trust your gut feeling. When you feel something feels off, perhaps it's not the answer yet. Search and question things, its okay to put your habit and behaviors under magnifying glass and wonder.

What if sometimes it worsens the condition, sometimes you are anxious to speak in front of people but sometimes the root of all issues could be your learning disorder, which can be mild and unnoticeable causing you self doubt and co-existing with anxiety.

Bipolar is similar to ADHD. The devil is in the details always and forever. 
 -Often in our need to get out of bad situation we apply a self diagnosis and look for tools to help it. How often have we heard, just stepping and doing will help our fears.

Cons ❌

-A lot of times people do not realise how much alot of similar medical conditions and other mental health mimic the same conditions. Anxiety can be a result of ADHD, as well as many other. Lead poisoning can cause similar behaviour as ADHD. BPD is similar to RSD.

-A lot of people don't even know they suffer from something until they go ask for physical diagnosis from doctors.
-It can help you feel assured, feel understood and have a sense of direction for future.
-A wrong path, might lead you to the right path in the end.

-A lot of people are in no position to get professional help, family issues and so on.
-Self Diagnosis can actually lead you to get an actual diagnosis, we all start with questions anyway. No one goes to therapist because they decided to for a cup of coffee.

Pros ✅
- No one knows better than yourself who are you. That is true, after all no one can sit in our mind and doctors have to ask us questions to get to know us. That's how we get to know everything, ask questions
- Doctors, assessments, therapies are expensive.

Self diagnosis pros ✅ and cons ❌
